## S48 [G28] Legacy 3-tier to 5-tier migration works
**Status:** in_progress
**Test File:** `backend/src/relay/config.rs` (inline `#[cfg(test)]`)
**Tags:** stack:backend, module:api-sources
**Depends on:** G28, D40

```rust
#[test]
fn test_legacy_tier_migration() {
    // Simulate loading legacy config with old 3-tier system
    let legacy_json = r#"[
        {
            "id": "legacy-source",
            "name": "Legacy",
            "provider": "Anthropic",
            "models": [
                {"id": "haiku", "name": "Haiku", "tier": "light"},
                {"id": "sonnet", "name": "Sonnet", "tier": "mid"},
                {"id": "opus", "name": "Opus", "tier": "heavy"}
            ]
        }
    ]"#;
    
    // Parse with support for legacy tiers
    let sources: Vec<ApiSource> = serde_json::from_str(legacy_json).unwrap();
    
    assert_eq!(sources[0].models[0].tier, ModelTier::Lite);  // light → Lite
    assert_eq!(sources[0].models[1].tier, ModelTier::Mid);    // mid → Mid
    assert_eq!(sources[0].models[2].tier, ModelTier::Large);  // heavy → Large
}
```

- Legacy "light" tier maps to Lite
- Legacy "mid" tier maps to Mid
- Legacy "heavy" tier maps to Large

