## S62 [G28] Multi-provider auto-detection finds all available providers on first startup
**Status:** draft
**Test File:** `backend/src/relay/config.rs` (inline `#[cfg(test)]`)
**Tags:** stack:backend, module:api-sources
**Depends on:** G28, D19

```rust
#[test]
fn test_auto_detect_anthropic_from_env() {
    // Set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY env var
    env::set_var("ANTHROPIC_API_KEY", "sk-test-key");
    
    let sources = detect_available_providers();
    
    assert!(sources.iter().any(|s| s.provider == Provider::Anthropic));
    let anthropic = sources.iter().find(|s| s.provider == Provider::Anthropic).unwrap();
    assert!(anthropic.is_available);
    assert_eq!(anthropic.api_key_env, "ANTHROPIC_API_KEY");
}

#[test]
fn test_auto_detect_openai_from_env() {
    env::set_var("OPENAI_API_KEY", "sk-openai-test");
    
    let sources = detect_available_providers();
    
    assert!(sources.iter().any(|s| s.provider == Provider::OpenAI));
    let openai = sources.iter().find(|s| s.provider == Provider::OpenAI).unwrap();
    assert!(openai.is_available);
}

#[test]
fn test_auto_detect_local_ollama() {
    // Mock localhost:11434 availability check
    // Returns true if Ollama is running
    let sources = detect_available_providers();
    
    if sources.iter().any(|s| s.provider == Provider::Local) {
        let local = sources.iter().find(|s| s.provider == Provider::Local).unwrap();
        assert_eq!(local.base_url, Some("http://localhost:11434".into()));
    }
}
```

- Anthropic provider detected when ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is set
- OpenAI provider detected when OPENAI_API_KEY is set
- Local/Ollama provider detected if localhost:11434 is reachable
- All detected providers have is_available = true

