## S64 [G28] Provider fallback chain works on API failure
**Status:** draft
**Test File:** `backend/src/ai.rs` (integration test)
**Tags:** stack:backend, module:api-sources
**Depends on:** G28, D20

```rust
#[test]
fn test_fallback_on_provider_failure() {
    let sources = vec![
        ApiSource {
            provider: Provider::Anthropic,
            is_available: false, // Simulate unavailable
            models: vec![ModelDefinition {
                id: "claude-3-5-sonnet".into(),
                tier: ModelTier::Mid,
                fallback_models: vec!["gpt-4o".into()],
                name: "Claude 3.5 Sonnet".into(),
            }],
        },
        ApiSource {
            provider: Provider::OpenAI,
            is_available: true,
            models: vec![ModelDefinition {
                id: "gpt-4o".into(),
                tier: ModelTier::Mid,
                name: "GPT-4o".into(),
            }],
        },
    ];
    
    let result = dispatch_chat_with_fallback(&sources, ModelTier::Mid, "test").await;
    
    assert!(result.is_ok());
    // Verify request fell back to OpenAI when Anthropic unavailable
}
```

- When primary provider fails, fallback models are tried
- Fallback chain respects tier constraints
- Returns error if all fallbacks fail

