## S66 [G28] AgentConfig resolution uses ApiSource-based model tiering
**Status:** draft
**Test File:** `backend/src/relay/agent.rs` (inline `#[cfg(test)]`)
**Tags:** stack:backend, module:api-sources
**Depends on:** G28, D40

```rust
#[test]
fn test_agent_uses_min_tier_for_gofer() {
    let gofer_profession = ProfessionRegistry::new().get("gofer").unwrap();
    let api_sources = vec![
        ApiSource {
            provider: Provider::Anthropic,
            models: vec![
                ModelDefinition {
                    id: "claude-3-5-haiku".into(),
                    tier: ModelTier::Min,
                    name: "Haiku".into(),
                },
                ModelDefinition {
                    id: "claude-3-5-sonnet".into(),
                    tier: ModelTier::Mid,
                    name: "Sonnet".into(),
                },
            ],
        },
    ];
    
    let agent = AgentInstance::spawn(gofer_profession, &api_sources).unwrap();
    
    assert_eq!(agent.model.id, "claude-3-5-haiku"); // Gofer gets Min tier
    assert_eq!(agent.model.tier, ModelTier::Min);
}

#[test]
fn test_agent_uses_large_tier_for_architect() {
    let architect_profession = ProfessionRegistry::new().get("architect").unwrap();
    let api_sources = vec![
        ApiSource {
            provider: Provider::Anthropic,
            models: vec![
                ModelDefinition {
                    id: "claude-3-opus".into(),
                    tier: ModelTier::Large,
                    name: "Opus".into(),
                },
            ],
        },
    ];
    
    let agent = AgentInstance::spawn(architect_profession, &api_sources).unwrap();
    
    assert_eq!(agent.model.tier, ModelTier::Large);
}
```

- Gofer profession resolves to Min tier model
- Architect profession resolves to Large tier model
- Agent uses provider with matching tier
- Falls back to next available tier if exact match unavailable

