## S68 [G38] HandoffNote injected as system message before next agent turn
**Status:** draft
**Test File:** `backend/src/forge/mod.rs` (integration test)
**Tags:** stack:backend, module:chat
**Depends on:** G38, D24

```rust
#[tokio::test]
async fn test_handoff_note_injection() {
    let mut session = ForgeSession::new("test-session");
    session.active_profession = Some("assistant".into());
    
    // Execute bring_in tool
    let result = session.execute_tool_call(json!({
        "name": "bring_in",
        "arguments": {
            "target": "advisor",
            "classification": "NEW_GOAL",
            "reason": "User wants OAuth2"
        }
    })).await.unwrap();
    
    // Verify handoff note added to messages
    let last_message = session.messages.last().unwrap();
    assert_eq!(last_message.role, "system");
    assert!(last_message.content.contains("Nicole (assistant) handed off to you"));
    assert!(last_message.content.contains("**Classification:** NEW_GOAL"));
    
    // Verify active_profession switched
    assert_eq!(session.active_profession, Some("advisor".into()));
}
```

- HandoffNote injected as system message after bring_in
- System message contains classification, reason, and context
- active_profession switched to new target
- Next agent turn sees handoff note in context

